node.text:
Our first ever adventure short is ready to go from swimming hole to summit and everything in between. We know there is no off-season for the dedicated shredder, and keeping the body moving is critical for a solid start to winter. 

DIVE IN 👉 https://bit.ly/3y95VI1

These shorts come fully loaded with 4-way stretch and quick drying DWR treated fabric that will leave you feeling unrestricted for whatever radness you get into 🤘

Early bird gets the worm. On this third and final segment of our Carinthia shoot, we woke up before the sun and wasted no time getting rowdy in the morning glow. 
Subaru of New England presents Promised Land: Season 2, the 15th annual production by Ski The East.  Featuring the Ski The East team traveling from Pennsylvania to Quebec in search of glory.

A Ski The East Web Series
Proudly Supported by:
@subaruofnewengland 
@k2.skis 
THIS EPISODE FEATURING

Fred Lavoie @fredlav13  Jacob Belanger @jacob_belanger  Andreya Zvonar @andreya_z  Bobby Sullivan @broccoli_bobby  Mac Forehand @macforehand 
Shot On Location At
Carinthia Parks, Mount Snow, Vermont

Special Thanks
Jamie Storrs

Filmed By
Cam Willis
Chris Dejohn
Zach Walbridge

Music
Layup - “Everybody’s Home”

node.text:
Ryan Hawks was a Vermonter that we were lucky enough to shred with and film with at his home mountain of Mad River Glen. He passed away after an injury sustained at a Freeride Competition stop in 2011 but his legacy lives on through the @flyinryanhawks . 
Ryan lived by these core values and the foundation's mission revolves around them.
"Live every day, all day
Never stop exploring life
Never lose my adventuresome spirit
Be the best friend I can be
Be the best brother, son, uncle I can be
Play like I am 13
Look out for others
Look out for myself
Look out for our surroundings
Be self-sufficient
Don’t be afraid to ask for help
Work hard
Live easy
Live simply"
Find more info about Ryan and the Flyin Ryan Foundation at https://flyinryanhawks.org/
